title: Billionaire
added: William G. Pete laid claim to an Asteroid 22786 Willipete<ref>{{cite web |title=22786 Willipete |url=https://ssd.jpl.nasa.gov/sbdb.cgi?sstr=22786 |website=NASA JPL |publisher=NASA JPL |accessdate=2 September 2020}}</ref> under H.R.2262, Title IV, Section 402 of the U.S. Commercial Space Launch Competitiveness Act of 2015 <ref>{{cite web |last1=McCarthy |first1=Kevin |title=H.R.2262 - U.S. Commercial Space Launch Competitiveness Act |url=https://www.congress.gov/bill/114th-congress/house-bill/2262 |website=Congress.gov |publisher=U.S. Congress |accessdate=2 September 2020}}</ref> "A U.S. citizen engaged in commercial recovery of an asteroid resource or a space resource shall be entitled to any asteroid resource or space resource obtained, including to possess, own, transport, use, and sell it according to applicable law, including U.S. international obligations." deriving a value of approximately $938 billion in proportionate value to other comparable asteroids such as 16 Psyche <ref>{{cite web |title=16 Psyche |url=https://solarsystem.nasa.gov/asteroids-comets-and-meteors/asteroids/16-psyche/in-depth/ |website=NASA.gov |publisher=NASA |accessdate=2 September 2020}}</ref>
